title: For Sale/Trade:  Springfield Armory XDS 3.3" .45
postcontent:
The XDS will come with everything SA ships with their pistols, double mag carrier, paddle holster etc. in the original box. It will also come with 2-5 round mags one of which has a pinky rest installed, and 1-7 round mag, all 3 factory. Along with that stuff I have a Blackhawk single mag carrier, and a brand new, never worn Alien Gear tuckable IWB holster (RH) I just received. This package is ready to be traded for or bought and carried the same day. 

The SA was one of the XDS' affected by the recall, but it has been sent in for the work. I have EXACTLY 150 rounds through this pistol, I keep a log on all my guns, and all of it was factory .45. No +p ammo was used.

There is a small mark on the left side of the slide, does not intefere with functrion at all, from where I had pocket carried it for a short time. I have learned that if you use the 5 round mag with the flat baseplate, this makes a nice pocket gun, and with summer coming up, who doesn't need a .45 caliber pocket gun?

The only reason I am looking to trade is I just prefer Glocks. Nothing wrong with this pistol at all, and the recoil on such a small pistol was suprisingly soft.

I am looking to trade this for a Glock in .45. My trade preferences, in order, are: Glock 41, Glock 21 Gen 4, Glock 21sf, Glock 30s, Glock 30sf, Glock 30 Gen 3, or maybe a Glock 36. I would be willing to accept one of these Glocks with only 2 factory mags, but I would prefer 3 and maybe a decent concealment holster, but it won't be a deal breaker if one is not included.

Now, I am not interested in a $700 Glock that has a "custom" stippling job, and I am eligible for Blue Label Glock purchases so try to keep that in mind if there are any trade offers. I can get a brand new Glock 21 or 41 Gen 4 for under 5 bills. 

Since I have to put a price on the XDS package, I will list it for $600 OBRO for the package, and remember that's with a seperate mag holder and brand new holster. (Just enough cash for a new BL Glock and a decent holster) 

Please gentlemen, the best way to reach me for pics, questions, or offers is through text at REDACTED, and thank you very much for looking.

title: For Sale:  COLT 1851 NAVY ANTIQUE/ORIGINAL
postcontent: The Colt Model 1851 Navy was Colt’s premier medium caliber percussion handgun. It was originally designed to be issued to the U. S. Navy, but the U. S. Army purchased most of the guns for their use, especially during the Civil War. It was manufactured from 1850-1873. A total of 215,348 were produced in the Hartford, Connecticut factory. By the end of the Civil War in December 1865, 185,000 had been produced. All 1851 Navy’s were .36 caliber, 6 shot 7.5 inch octagon barrels with attached loading levers. Grips were one piece walnut. Grip straps were silver plated brass. The trigger guard was a large round trigger guard. Three basic barrel markings were used. The standard cylinder scene was the battle between the Texas Navy and Mexico. This particular Colt Model 1851 Navy appears to be all original and is the 4th model with the wedge screw above the wedge. It is not in pristine condition because of its age and use. It was manufactured in 1866 bearing all matching serial number 192,383. It is .36 caliber, 6 shot, 7.5” octagon barrel with legible address marking: ADDRESS COL. SAML. COLT NEW-YORK U.S. AMERICA. Stamped on the left side of the frame: COLTS/PATENT. Has a nice dark patina. One piece walnut wood grips. Mellow brass straps. Cocks and locks up tight. All nipples present and in good condition. No cylinder scene, but faint date marking. A good collectible, authentic, original Colt Model 1851 Navy. NOT FOR FIRING. COLLECTIBLE ONLY. SHIPS DIRECTLY TO BUYER. NO FFL. SHIPPING INCLUDED IN PRICE!
